                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>\n                <date>May 17. 1852</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev'd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I wrote you near two weeks since, which<lb/> suppose you have\n                received;—since which I received your<lb/>\n                <date><sic>may</sic></date> Occident, in addition to the old list, you sent to<lb/>\n                <persName>Messrs. Hechimer </persName> &amp; <persName>Goldsmith</persName>, &amp;\n                    <persName>S &amp; W Shroeder</persName>, I sent them<lb/> &amp; they were\n                returned to me, you had better not send to<lb/> nay new names, without they are sent\n                for; or<lb/> ordered through me:—I have sold 3 Prayer Books;—</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mr Rosenfeldt</persName> request me to order on from\n                you<lb/> 6 (six) dozen 'Scriptural Questions for the use of<lb/> Sunday Schools'\n                compiled by <persName>E Pike</persName>.—<lb/> and 3 (three) Dozen of <persName>Mr\n                    Nathan's</persName> Road to Faith, if they<lb/> can be got, 100 copies would be\n                too many at present,<lb/> the expense would have to be born by 2 or 3\n                Individuals,<lb/> excepting those that are paid for; <persName>Mr\n                    Rosenfeldt's</persName> con-<lb/>gregation provides no Teachers, (<persName>Mr\n                        Kub<add>?</add></persName> having withdrawn)<lb/> and our Congregation being\n                set against it, by the <hi rend=\"underline\">pious</hi><lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Mabzu</persName>; I have found your list of Debtors since<lb/> I last\n                wrote &amp; will endeavor to make collections;<lb/> The Sunday School still contains\n                upwards of 100 children;<lb/> The Hebrew Gentlemen's Benevolent Society, at\n                their<lb/> last Election, Elected <persName>Mosely Ezekiel Esq.</persName> President<lb/>\n                <persName>Henry Mack Esq.</persName> Vice President. <persName>Isaac\n                    Hackenberg</persName> Treasr.<lb/>\n                <persName>Henry Harris Esq.</persName> Sect.—Hebrew Ladies Benevolent Soceity<lb/>\n                PYO</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p31j97v1t/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
